text: Emil Bottlang (born December 23, 1912, date of death unknown) is a Swiss canoeist who competed from the late 1930s to the late 1940s. Competing in two Summer Olympics, he earned his best finish of sixth in the folding K-2 10000 m event at Berlin in 1936. ==References== *Sports-reference.com profile Category:1912 births Category:Canoeists at the 1936 Summer Olympics Category:Canoeists at the 1948 Summer Olympics Category:Olympic canoeists of Switzerland Category:Year of death missing Category:Swiss male canoeists
